// Details for: soundcore-space-one-headphones (Soundcore Space One, model A3035)
// Lab sheet: CV-EB-A3035-001 — §7.5 ELEVATED gold deepen (Wave Mid product 5/8).
//   Upgraded from the first protocol-grade bench (~151 lines) that already held
//   Timer+ AAC/LDAC × ANC OFF/ON stopwatches, Kkmoon weight, FNB58 charge, BT
//   walk, and Egypt field ANC notes. This pass adds sibling A/B ladder hygiene
//   vs Q20i / Q30 / Q45, soft-pouch vs hard-case trade, airline cabin note, and
//   speech-band honesty — WITHOUT inventing new dB / ms / SNR and WITHOUT
//   pasting sibling stopwatch rows as this sample's own numbers.
//   Any vendor "% noise reduction" / dB figure = vendor-stated only (§11.3 / §14).
// Wave headphones (over-ear). Physics envelope enforced (§8). §7.5 adapted for
//   over-ear / on-ear: A = full-unit weight (no buds/case split); B = playtime
//   AAC ANC OFF + Adaptive ANC ON (+ LDAC differentials); C/E case steps = N/A
//   (no charging case); D/F = USB-C full + quick charge on the unit; G = BT
//   range; H = multipoint (with LDAC exclusivity note); I = ANC qualitative
//   only (no anechoic / no invented dB); J = mic qualitative (no SNR); K =
//   codecs in Soundcore App (LDAC ladder on Android); L = latency qualitative
//   (no ms).
// Sibling ladder: Q20i (A3004, hybrid ANC + soft pouch, no LDAC) → Life Q30
//   (A3028, Transport/Indoor/Outdoor + hard case, no LDAC) → Space One (A3035,
//   Adaptive ANC + LDAC + soft pouch, this file) → Space Q45 (A3040, Adaptive
//   ANC + LDAC + hard case, longer vendor cell). Sibling files untouched.
// CairoVolt is an INDEPENDENT retailer — not an authorized/official distributor.
